WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:05.804
♪♪

00:05.806 --> 00:07.272
Clef: ♪ Oh, my darling ♪

00:07.274 --> 00:09.007
♪ Oh, my darling ♪

00:09.009 --> 00:13.145
♪ Oh, my darling, Clementine ♪

00:13.147 --> 00:15.614
♪ You are lost and gone for-- ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:25.423
♪♪

00:25.425 --> 00:28.360
[ Engine revs ]

00:43.778 --> 00:46.779
These armadillos are getting
to be a goddamn menace.

00:46.781 --> 00:51.383
Why don't they just build cars
out of armadillo skin?

00:51.385 --> 00:52.717
Well, shit, Larry.

00:52.719 --> 00:55.253
That's a million-dollar idea
you got there.

00:55.255 --> 00:59.258
It'd be a real shame
if someone...stole it from ya.

01:01.462 --> 01:03.128
Someone's coming.

01:03.130 --> 01:11.736
♪♪

01:11.738 --> 01:19.944
♪♪

01:19.946 --> 01:28.286
♪♪

01:28.288 --> 01:36.695
♪♪

01:36.697 --> 01:45.103
♪♪

01:45.105 --> 01:53.311
♪♪

01:53.313 --> 01:55.647
[ Clears throat ]

01:55.649 --> 02:00.985
♪♪

02:00.987 --> 02:03.321
Afternoon, boys.

02:03.323 --> 02:04.857
I appreciate your service,

02:04.859 --> 02:08.494
but I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to take it from here.

02:11.665 --> 02:13.598
Fine by us.

02:13.600 --> 02:15.267
I said, I'm gonna
take it from here!

02:15.269 --> 02:16.869
[ Electricity zaps ]

02:16.871 --> 02:19.204
♪♪

02:19.206 --> 02:20.939
[ Gunshot fires ]

02:20.941 --> 02:23.475
♪♪

02:23.477 --> 02:25.610
I've recently been handed
a rather bleak diagnosis

02:25.612 --> 02:27.679
and may not have much
longer on this earth,

02:27.681 --> 02:32.384
so I thought to myself, what a
perfect time to adopt a baby.

02:34.488 --> 02:36.621
What's going on here?

02:36.623 --> 02:39.224
What is
the Special Division Force?

02:39.226 --> 02:41.826
I told you,
we take on cases --

02:41.828 --> 02:43.762
I know what the official
explanation is,

02:43.764 --> 02:45.830
but I want to know
what we're really doing.

02:45.832 --> 02:48.500
Right now,
our only job is to follow

02:48.502 --> 02:50.302
the orders
of the Vice President.

02:50.304 --> 02:51.836
Vice President Perry?

02:51.838 --> 02:53.906
The man who not only
threw me into jail

02:53.908 --> 02:56.308
but whose administration
has been plagued by scandal

02:56.310 --> 02:57.509
since he was elected?

02:57.511 --> 02:58.977
He's no
John Nance Garner,

02:58.979 --> 03:01.179
but he's the only
Vice President we've got!

03:01.181 --> 03:02.847
John Nance Garner?

03:02.849 --> 03:05.850
He's barely
Schuyler Colfax.

03:05.852 --> 03:11.523
Sir, how do we know
if we're even the good guys?

03:11.525 --> 03:14.827
Tribeca,
look me in the eye.

03:17.998 --> 03:20.865
We are the good guys.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.935
I stole the dead teacher
from the cops.

03:22.937 --> 03:24.403
Now what?

03:31.478 --> 03:33.678
His name is Charlie Clef.

03:33.680 --> 03:35.280
Come on, Hoffman.
Sorry, Murphy.

03:35.282 --> 03:37.015
Above your pay grade.

03:37.017 --> 03:38.950
He was a beloved
computer science teacher

03:38.952 --> 03:43.021
at Freddie Prinze Junior Senior
High School in Amarillo, Texas.

03:43.023 --> 03:44.890
He was also the most
prolific distributor

03:44.892 --> 03:47.826
of malware and computer exploits
in the Northern Hemisphere.

03:47.828 --> 03:50.295
His clients included
terrorist organizations,

03:50.297 --> 03:51.630
hostile
foreign governments,

03:51.632 --> 03:53.498
and people who want
to see celebrities naked.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.500
So now he's dead.
End of story, right?

03:55.502 --> 03:57.836
Wrong.
Beginning of story.

03:57.838 --> 03:59.838
Clef had just put
the finishing touches

03:59.840 --> 04:02.641
on a particularly
damaging computer virus.

04:02.643 --> 04:04.776
The kind of thing that
shuts down power grids

04:04.778 --> 04:07.713
and publishes
your browsing history.

04:07.715 --> 04:10.049
So now he's dead.
End of story, right?

04:10.051 --> 04:11.182
Wrong!

04:11.184 --> 04:13.118
Middle of story!

04:13.120 --> 04:16.121
His death provides us
with a unique opportunity

04:16.123 --> 04:19.658
to take his place and flush out
a high-profile buyer

04:19.660 --> 04:21.526
who recently
expressed interest in --

04:21.528 --> 04:22.861
what was the name
of the virus?

04:22.863 --> 04:23.929
LamarModem.

04:23.931 --> 04:26.197
Tribeca will impersonate Clef

04:26.199 --> 04:27.999
and try to make contact
with the buyer

04:28.001 --> 04:30.669
while the rest of us infiltrate
the high school genre

04:30.671 --> 04:32.070
in supporting roles.

04:32.072 --> 04:33.272
I have one question.

04:33.274 --> 04:34.339
One sec.

04:34.341 --> 04:35.674
Any questions?
Uh, yes.

04:35.676 --> 04:36.875
Will you be taking
questions?

04:36.877 --> 04:38.410
At the end.
Anything else?

04:38.412 --> 04:40.345
Is Vice President Perry
a crook?

04:40.347 --> 04:42.681
I am warning you, Tribeca!

04:42.683 --> 04:45.417
Now get to Prosthetics
for your disguise fitting!

04:45.419 --> 04:46.785
Yes, sir.

04:48.822 --> 04:50.756
Hey. What the hell
is with you?

04:50.758 --> 04:52.291
Don't talk to me
like that.

04:52.293 --> 04:53.758
I didn't raise you
to be disrespectful.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.294
You didn't raise me
at all.

04:55.296 --> 04:56.628
So it didn't
come from me.

04:56.630 --> 04:58.697
Look, I-I read
your autobiography, okay?

04:58.699 --> 05:00.699
I know that you're
a lone wolf that --

05:00.701 --> 05:02.101
that doesn't trust
the system,

05:02.103 --> 05:03.568
but I care about
what we're doing,

05:03.570 --> 05:05.170
and I expect you
to care about it, too.

05:05.172 --> 05:06.772
Maybe I'll care
if I can figure out

05:06.774 --> 05:08.573
if we're actually fighting
for the right side.

05:08.575 --> 05:09.508
Oh, okay, well,
that's just great.

05:09.510 --> 05:11.042
Well, you know what?

05:11.044 --> 05:12.377
Besides my birth,
this is the first thing you

05:12.379 --> 05:13.912
and I have done
as mother and son.

05:13.914 --> 05:16.781
And if that's not enough for you
to care about this,

05:16.783 --> 05:18.850
then I guess
it's high time

05:18.852 --> 05:20.385
I pick up
a few bad habits

05:20.387 --> 05:23.254
and fall in
with the wrong crowd.

05:23.256 --> 05:26.625
[ Skateboard wheels whir ]

05:32.399 --> 05:35.934
[ Fast-paced piano music
playing ]

05:35.936 --> 05:41.573
♪♪

05:44.277 --> 05:45.711
Let's do this.

05:47.681 --> 05:50.081
You were born Charles
John Jacob Jingleheimer Clef

05:50.083 --> 05:53.819
in Plano, Texas,
on December 12, 1961.

05:53.821 --> 05:56.087
As an only child, you craved
your parents' approval,

05:56.089 --> 05:59.224
and as an adult, you seek that
approval from your students.

05:59.226 --> 06:01.292
Your intellectual
proclivities unfulfilled

06:01.294 --> 06:04.163
by the banal environment
of secondary education,

06:04.165 --> 06:05.630
you turned to the more
challenging world

06:05.632 --> 06:08.167
of malevolent
software programming.

06:08.169 --> 06:10.902
Favorite food -- pizza.

06:10.904 --> 06:12.705
Let's see what we got.

06:16.577 --> 06:18.577
Perfect.
Wow.

06:18.579 --> 06:20.311
This is going to take
some getting used to.

06:20.313 --> 06:23.182
Now, remember, kids are
very different nowadays.

06:23.184 --> 06:25.717
They're very confident,
they're sex-positive,

06:25.719 --> 06:27.186
they're body-positive.

06:27.188 --> 06:29.654
And some of them have
unwarranted high self-esteem.

06:29.656 --> 06:31.790
If it's so unwarranted,
why am I so great?

06:31.792 --> 06:35.527
Good luck, Tribeca.

06:35.529 --> 06:36.395
Or should I say...?

06:36.397 --> 06:38.329
Mr. Clef?

06:38.331 --> 06:39.398
Yes, Delroy?

06:39.400 --> 06:41.800
I can't get
my subroutine to run.

06:41.802 --> 06:44.335
Looks like there's
a parsing error in line 19.

06:44.337 --> 06:47.472
What's the error?
Well,
if I told you that...

06:47.474 --> 06:49.007
You wouldn't be teaching,
you'd be telling.
I wouldn't be teaching,
I'd be telling.

06:49.009 --> 06:51.342
That's right.
[ Bell rings ]

06:51.344 --> 06:54.413
All right, everybody,
websites are due Friday.

06:54.415 --> 06:57.816
Mr. C., can I --
No, Tommy,
you cannot have an extension.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.952
You're the best, Mr. C.

07:02.556 --> 07:05.024
Charo, Scholls,
you're geniuses.

07:05.026 --> 07:07.793
This is going to be
a piece of cake.

07:09.563 --> 07:11.030
I knew it.

07:11.032 --> 07:13.565
Come on, Mr. Clef, we're gonna
be late for practice.

07:13.567 --> 07:14.699
What practice?

07:14.701 --> 07:16.701
[ Laughs ]

07:16.703 --> 07:18.637
You're so funny, Mr. C.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.305
Glee Club practice.

07:20.307 --> 07:23.042
You're the coach.

07:23.044 --> 07:26.245
[ Laughs ]

07:26.247 --> 07:27.646
We've got a problem.

07:27.648 --> 07:28.881
[ Bell rings ]

07:32.586 --> 07:34.319
Man:<i> It's a beautiful day</i>
<i> for football practice</i>

07:34.321 --> 07:36.254
<i> as the Freddie Prinze Junior</i>
<i> Senior High squad</i>

07:36.256 --> 07:39.191
<i> runs their plays</i>
<i> against a mock defense.</i>

07:39.193 --> 07:41.193
<i> But the team's</i>
<i> in some hot water this week</i>

07:41.195 --> 07:43.461
<i> after a local paper</i>
<i> ran an editorial</i>

07:43.463 --> 07:45.197
<i> suggesting</i>
<i> that their team name</i>

07:45.199 --> 07:47.132
<i> was offensive</i>
<i> to Native Americans.</i>

07:47.134 --> 07:49.267
<i> I don't know how they got there</i>
<i> from Drunken Injuns,</i>

07:49.269 --> 07:51.136
<i> but, hey, I'm just</i>
<i> a football fan.</i>

07:51.138 --> 07:52.337
[ Whistle blows ]

07:52.339 --> 07:55.941
No! Jesus!

07:55.943 --> 07:59.344
Eleven,
get your ass over here!

07:59.346 --> 08:00.546
[ Spits ]

08:00.548 --> 08:01.880
It's a simple read option!

08:01.882 --> 08:03.215
You look for the hole!

08:03.217 --> 08:06.017
If it's not there, you pitch
to the running back!

08:06.019 --> 08:07.285
Durphy
wasn't in position --

08:07.287 --> 08:08.353
I don't want to hear
about Durphy!

08:08.355 --> 08:09.821
His parents
are divorcing!

08:09.823 --> 08:12.424
He may be a step
behind for a while!

08:14.962 --> 08:18.096
Your dad cheated on your mom,
so she's kicking him out.

08:18.098 --> 08:20.899
But that's not your fault,
so don't take that on.

08:20.901 --> 08:22.367
Thanks, Coach.

08:22.369 --> 08:24.502
Hit the showers, buddy.

08:24.504 --> 08:27.039
[ Whistle blows ]
Now run it again!

08:27.041 --> 08:29.775
This time with your head
on the outside of your ass!

08:29.777 --> 08:32.377
Yes, sir.

08:32.379 --> 08:34.646
[ Cellphone rings ]
This is Coach.

08:34.648 --> 08:35.781
Oh, hey, Coach.

08:35.783 --> 08:37.115
It's Mr. Clef,

08:37.117 --> 08:38.984
who, when he's not busy
selling malware,

08:38.986 --> 08:42.720
apparently runs the Glee Club.

08:42.722 --> 08:43.855
Damn it!

08:43.857 --> 08:44.990
How did we not
see that coming?

08:44.992 --> 08:46.792
I don't know,
but I did not study up

08:46.794 --> 08:48.460
on anything
but computer science.

08:48.462 --> 08:51.263
I don't know anything about
F sharps and G minuses.

08:51.265 --> 08:53.064
Look, Tribeca,
we are here

08:53.066 --> 08:54.733
to stop the spread
of computer viruses,

08:54.735 --> 08:58.003
so you just hang on until you
get contacted by the buyer.

08:58.005 --> 09:01.206
And then we will tell the kids
their teacher is dead

09:01.208 --> 09:03.541
and we will get
the hell out of here.

09:03.543 --> 09:05.611
Fine.

09:05.613 --> 09:07.345
All right, everyone.

09:07.347 --> 09:11.083
Well, obviously I know your
names, but maybe just for fun,

09:11.085 --> 09:12.818
you guys can sing your name

09:12.820 --> 09:16.554
and then the thing you're gonna
overcome before the big concert.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.756
[ Off-key ]
♪ I'm Maria ♪

09:18.758 --> 09:20.826
♪ Pills and depression ♪

09:20.828 --> 09:23.095
♪ I eat my own hair ♪

09:23.097 --> 09:24.763
♪ My uncle makes me -- ♪

09:24.765 --> 09:27.699
Okay, all right. Next.
[ Off-key ] ♪ I'm Pradeep ♪

09:27.701 --> 09:30.969
♪ Arranged marriage to
a girl that I do not love ♪

09:30.971 --> 09:32.504
Peter: ♪ I'm Peter ♪

09:32.506 --> 09:35.707
♪ And there's a [bleep]
in my locker ♪

09:35.709 --> 09:41.179
♪ I'm Grace and I'm pregnant
with Pradeep's baby ♪

09:41.181 --> 09:43.048
We don't need to
hear from everyone.

09:43.050 --> 09:45.250
All right,
so, should we, uh,

09:45.252 --> 09:47.986
pick it up from where we
left off last practice?

09:47.988 --> 09:50.322
Last practice you said
that you were going to write

09:50.324 --> 09:51.589
a brand-new song
for us to try.

09:51.591 --> 09:53.391
I did.
I did.

09:53.393 --> 09:56.128
Okay.
Um, and yes, here it is.

09:56.130 --> 09:57.863
I hope that you like it.

09:57.865 --> 10:00.799
[ Clears throat ]

10:00.801 --> 10:05.203
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

10:05.205 --> 10:08.940
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

10:08.942 --> 10:12.878
♪ Happy birthday,
happy birthday ♪

10:12.880 --> 10:18.016
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

10:18.018 --> 10:19.485
Oh, my God.

10:19.487 --> 10:21.019
I love it.

10:21.021 --> 10:22.087
All right, great.

10:22.089 --> 10:23.889
All right,
should we try it?

10:23.891 --> 10:27.559
Okay.
And a one and a two and a --

10:27.561 --> 10:31.296
[ All singing off-key ]

10:34.902 --> 10:36.568
My water just broke!

10:37.705 --> 10:41.106
[ Bell rings ]
No, sir, I have not heard
from the buyer yet,

10:41.108 --> 10:42.974
but I did listen
to the worst singers

10:42.976 --> 10:44.109
in the history of the world.

10:44.111 --> 10:47.245
I delivered a baby and --
Yeah, I can ask,

10:47.247 --> 10:49.781
but I think
the grandmother's raising it.

10:49.783 --> 10:55.120
Now, if I could just find some
decent confiscated snacks...

10:55.122 --> 10:58.256
And paydirt.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.526
All right, I'll talk
to you tomorrow.

11:00.528 --> 11:01.860
Okay, love you too.

11:01.862 --> 11:02.928
[ Chat alert beeps ]

11:02.930 --> 11:11.603
♪♪

11:11.605 --> 11:20.478
♪♪

11:20.480 --> 11:28.887
♪♪

11:28.889 --> 11:37.563
♪♪

11:37.565 --> 11:46.438
♪♪

11:46.440 --> 11:54.913
♪♪

11:54.915 --> 12:03.721
♪♪

12:03.723 --> 12:12.197
♪♪

12:12.199 --> 12:14.266
[ Bell rings ]

12:14.268 --> 12:16.935
Hey, what the hell happened
with tracking my target?

12:16.937 --> 12:18.203
He got totally spooked.

12:18.205 --> 12:19.871
Now, now, Tribeca,
have a seat.

12:19.873 --> 12:21.407
Help yourself to a burger.

12:21.409 --> 12:24.542
I don't want to point any
fingers, but she messed up.

12:24.544 --> 12:27.145
Atkins: Let's not play
the blame game!

12:27.147 --> 12:28.280
Always takes forever.

12:28.282 --> 12:29.748
How about
Cards Against Humanity?

12:29.750 --> 12:33.485
I masked my IP address with
triple DES 168-bit encryption.

12:33.487 --> 12:36.622
My little brother has triple
DES 168-bit encryption.

12:36.624 --> 12:38.624
Your technology
is so two days ago.

12:38.626 --> 12:40.158
At least
I've lost my virginity.

12:40.160 --> 12:41.827
So have I.
He just lives in Europe.

12:41.829 --> 12:44.162
Knock it off, you two!

12:44.164 --> 12:45.897
Oh, it's eight players.
That won't work.

12:45.899 --> 12:49.101
It'll be a miracle if he shows
up at the loading dock tonight.

12:49.103 --> 12:52.170
Where's A.J.? School was out
like 20 minutes ago.

12:52.172 --> 12:54.106
I'm afraid A.J.'s having
a hard time here.

12:54.108 --> 12:56.842
He's fallen in
with a bad crowd.

12:56.844 --> 13:05.583
♪♪

13:05.585 --> 13:08.386
Oh, Lana likes
what she sees.

13:08.388 --> 13:10.522
I don't know
about these clothes.
Oh, trust me.

13:10.524 --> 13:12.590
Those shorts squeeze you
in all the right places,

13:12.592 --> 13:17.129
and in one place
that's very, very wrong.

13:17.131 --> 13:19.064
Here.
Take a hit of this.

13:19.066 --> 13:20.732
What's in that?
Nothing much.

13:20.734 --> 13:25.070
Glucose, Electrolytes,
some B vitamins.

13:25.072 --> 13:26.938
What if they test my urine?

13:26.940 --> 13:29.008
That's what this is for.

13:30.810 --> 13:33.278
That's a clean urine
in case they test you.

13:33.280 --> 13:36.548
Yeah, I know, I know.

13:36.550 --> 13:39.151
Okay, guys,
let's log some miles.

13:39.153 --> 13:40.285
What are you doing?

13:40.287 --> 13:41.753
Oh, shoot, it's my mom.

13:41.755 --> 13:43.288
Wait,
Mr. Clef is your mom?

13:43.290 --> 13:46.224
No, I meant to say my moon.

13:46.226 --> 13:48.426
Mr. Clef is your moon?
That sucks.

13:48.428 --> 13:50.095
Where do you think
you're going?

13:50.097 --> 13:51.697
You are gonna
get off that bike

13:51.699 --> 13:53.298
and you're coming
with me this minute.

13:53.300 --> 13:56.968
The only place he's going
is Stoneybrook Bike Path.

13:56.970 --> 13:58.504
So back off, old man.

13:58.506 --> 14:00.305
I would watch that mouth,
young lady.

14:00.307 --> 14:02.574
What are you gonna do? I'm
already accepted at Stanford.

14:02.576 --> 14:03.842
You look ridiculous.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.511
This is how you want
to spend your time?

14:05.513 --> 14:07.779
At least these people believe
in what they're doing.

14:07.781 --> 14:10.315
All right, let's go, A.J.
And you know what?

14:10.317 --> 14:12.450
If you do
a good job today,

14:12.452 --> 14:14.186
I'm gonna teach you
how to shave your legs.

14:14.188 --> 14:18.256
♪♪

14:18.258 --> 14:20.592
Sorry, Mr. Clef.

14:20.594 --> 14:22.127
I got to go.

14:22.129 --> 14:24.996
[ Coughs ]

14:24.998 --> 14:27.399
[ Horn honks ]
Hey, hey, hey!
What are you doing?

14:27.401 --> 14:28.934
[ Bell rings ]

14:28.936 --> 14:30.135
You wanted to see me, sir?

14:30.137 --> 14:32.538
Yeah, Scholls, come on in.
Take a knee.

14:32.540 --> 14:37.675
♪♪

14:37.677 --> 14:39.677
You know, this is a big case
we got going on here,

14:39.679 --> 14:42.480
and there's a lot of
pressure on everybody.
Yes, sir.

14:42.482 --> 14:44.750
I'm just a little worried
your head's not totally in it.

14:44.752 --> 14:46.351
Charo gets under my skin.

14:46.353 --> 14:48.286
Charo's young.
She's hungry.

14:48.288 --> 14:50.288
You just concentrate
on what you have --

14:50.290 --> 14:52.758
wisdom, experience,
and a smile

14:52.760 --> 14:55.227
that could light up
New York City.

14:55.229 --> 14:57.429
Okay. I'll try.

14:57.431 --> 14:59.297
Hey!
You can leave "try"

14:59.299 --> 15:00.498
out there
with the dirty jock straps!

15:00.500 --> 15:02.700
You get 'er done,
you hear?!

15:02.702 --> 15:05.304
Yes, sir!
Now drop and give me 20!

15:07.641 --> 15:12.244
♪♪

15:12.246 --> 15:15.046
Merlot: [ French accent ]
Hello, Mr. Clef.

15:15.048 --> 15:16.314
Who's there?

15:16.316 --> 15:17.983
I am Claude Merlot.

15:17.985 --> 15:19.317
Do you have the virus?

15:19.319 --> 15:21.319
Where are you?
I can't see you.

15:21.321 --> 15:23.855
Do you have the virus?

15:23.857 --> 15:26.391
Yes, I have it right here.

15:26.393 --> 15:28.460
But you need
to expose yourself.

15:28.462 --> 15:32.530
Okay, I'm doing it.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.132
Put the virus
on the ground.

15:34.134 --> 15:35.533
Not until I see your face.

15:35.535 --> 15:38.536
The National Glee Club
Championship is tomorrow.

15:38.538 --> 15:41.473
This high school has won
every year the past 12 years

15:41.475 --> 15:44.409
under Charlie Clef's
coaching.

15:44.411 --> 15:48.280
If you are who you say you are,
your team will win,

15:48.282 --> 15:50.415
and then we will
make the exchange.

15:50.417 --> 15:52.418
Yeah, well, if that's
what you want, fine.

15:52.420 --> 15:53.885
It's no problem with me.

15:53.887 --> 15:55.687
I mean, I was planning
on winning anyway.

15:55.689 --> 15:58.223
Until tomorrow then.

15:58.225 --> 16:01.193
By the way, I am not
in this Dumpster.

16:04.765 --> 16:08.099
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

16:08.101 --> 16:09.701
♪ Happy birthday ♪

16:09.703 --> 16:11.837
♪ Happy birthday ♪
Tribeca: No, no, no!

16:11.839 --> 16:13.038
No! No!

16:13.040 --> 16:15.707
You're sharp, you're flat,
you're breastfeeding,

16:15.709 --> 16:16.975
and you're, like, amazing.

16:16.977 --> 16:19.244
Oh, I know.
I was just faking it before.

16:19.246 --> 16:23.448
What is it going to take for you
people to get your act together?

16:23.450 --> 16:26.051
Peter, if you miss
your mark one more time,

16:26.053 --> 16:28.653
I am going to thwack you over
the head with your own [bleep]

16:28.655 --> 16:31.190
I am trying, okay?
Todd's wheelchair is in the way.

16:31.192 --> 16:34.325
Seriously, Todd, just stand up
and do the choreography.

16:34.327 --> 16:36.795
Whoa,
that is way out of line.

16:36.797 --> 16:38.530
Todd has Plantar Fasciitis,
okay?

16:38.532 --> 16:41.666
You have no idea what it's like
to be in his orthotic shoes.

16:41.668 --> 16:43.068
I'm okay.

16:43.070 --> 16:44.803
I'm sorry.

16:44.805 --> 16:46.738
Okay?

16:46.740 --> 16:49.674
I'm guessing that I used to be
really good with kids,

16:49.676 --> 16:53.879
but the Mr. Clef
who woke up yesterday morning

16:53.881 --> 16:57.549
doesn't have a clue about
how to connect with a child.

16:57.551 --> 16:59.684
I thought it'd be easy,
you know.

16:59.686 --> 17:04.556
Feed them, water them,
shear them when they get woolly.

17:04.558 --> 17:08.093
But it turns out...

17:08.095 --> 17:10.028
it's more than just that.

17:10.030 --> 17:13.899
You have to listen to them
and you have to pretend

17:13.901 --> 17:16.335
the things they care about
aren't stupid.

17:18.839 --> 17:21.973
Well, that doesn't
come easily to me.

17:21.975 --> 17:25.110
Suddenly,
in the last two days.

17:25.112 --> 17:27.846
But the National Championships
are this afternoon,

17:27.848 --> 17:31.783
and the stakes of winning
have never been higher.

17:31.785 --> 17:33.652
So let's make a deal.

17:33.654 --> 17:36.387
You guys try not to be terrible,

17:36.389 --> 17:37.990
and that would be great.

17:41.328 --> 17:42.394
Who's in?

17:42.396 --> 17:46.065
[ Slow clapping ]

17:47.401 --> 17:48.600
Sorry.

17:50.271 --> 17:52.471
♪ Oh, doo-dah day ♪

17:52.473 --> 17:54.539
♪ Going to run all night ♪

17:54.541 --> 17:56.808
♪ Going to run all day ♪

17:56.810 --> 17:58.944
♪ Bet my money
on a bob-tail nag ♪

17:58.946 --> 18:01.546
♪ Somebody bet on the bay ♪

18:01.548 --> 18:04.750
[ Cheers and applause ]

18:09.222 --> 18:11.490
I hate to say it,
but I think we have no chance

18:11.492 --> 18:13.158
of winning
this tournament.

18:13.160 --> 18:15.160
Merlot's gonna know
I'm not the real Clef.

18:15.162 --> 18:16.161
Stop eating your hair!

18:16.163 --> 18:17.696
I can't!

18:17.698 --> 18:19.965
Announcer: And now,
the final club of the night,

18:19.967 --> 18:23.034
the 12-time defending
national champions,

18:23.036 --> 18:25.570
The Freddie Prinze Junior
Senior High School

18:25.572 --> 18:27.438
Martha Plimp-tones.

18:27.440 --> 18:31.710
[ Cheers and applause ]

